<br>
To the original poster, I'll say i'm sorry you had a rough time when we were moving through that area (and it was an expecially long, greuling time getting everyone together).  As for all the complaints you had and your conclusion that TWC leadership is to blame, I have to note that you nor anyone else ever contacted me or any other officer regarding your specific or the general situation at all. <br>
<br>
Flame and vitrol in /ooc will earn you no &quot;respect&quot; in game and earn you no special considerations, similar to the reaction you have provoked here out of game.  Personally I suspect you're probably not a very pleasant person to be around in even the best of times.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, regarding this situation, I'll say that I dont know of any solutions that would not guarantee a similar or repeat performance of this kind of thing in the future.  And as evidenced here, it seems that no guild has the answer to this particular problem.  Do like everyone else and blame Sony, i suppose, it's their world after all.  I can however guarantee that respectful and calm complaints directed to me and I would hope any of the other officers of TWC will be responded to with honest and sincere efforts to remedy any damages that might have been done and to avoid further problems.<br>
<br>
<br>
Flame threads are always the best, and though it is completely pointless I want to comment on some of the other things mentioned in this thread.<br>
<br>
Yes TWC is about as old a guild as there are in EQ.  I joined it in late '99 some time.  Actually I'm still upset our reform cost us our place in the guild file, and you can no longer get a list of TWC members with &quot;/ all the&quot;.  There are a handful of members who are still in TWC that are founding members or have been in as long as I have.  I've been GL technically for a bit over a year, and defacto GL for good portions of half a year to a year before that.  The very vast majority of members are relative &quot;newcomers&quot; in the guild.<br>
<br>
As for turnover, hehe seems like over half the server has been in TWC.  Recently though I would consider our retention to be as high as can be realisticly expected.  The guild is stronger than it has ever been, and by a very large margin at that.<br>
<br>
To the haters, we ask not for your sympathy.  It's not worth much anyway.<br>
