<br>
 There is a pretty reliable method of crossing the river with either no aggro, or maybe an alligator at most aggroing if you lose too much height too quickly.<br>
<br>
1)Follow the zone wall until you see the canyon edge.<br>
<br>
2)Stay a good distance from the edge and follow the canyon out into the zone until you reach the first large boulder sitting at the edge of the canyon.<br>
<br>
3) Face the river and look for the tree on the other side.<br>
<br>
4) Run to that tree, turn and check for aggro.  <br>
<br>
 Usually there is none, at most you'll have one critter to deal with.   If you don't get that far from the zone wall though, you *will* aggro hobgoblins, which are the worst thing you can aggro while crossing the river.  That's what causes most trains.<br>
<br>
 Hope this helps someone. <br>
<br>
 Zandramas<br>
