<br>
It goes without saying that you should have lev on, doesn't it?<br>
<br>
Yes, it's always possible to draw random aggro on that trip.  You might not run high enough, or you come too close to the hobgoblins, or you just get unlucky somehow.  But you can avoid 95% of the aggro, and 95% of the trains, that way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=articnv>articnv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(6/13/03 7:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3306.topic&index=54>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Beth adding me to what list and for what  i m cvonfused <p><body>
